Package nz.ac.auckland.morc

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    morc
    A convenience class that helps to quickly instantiate test cases using a scripting tool like Groovy.
    MorcBuilder<Builder extends MorcBuilder<Builder>>
    The root builder for specifying processors and predicates for message publishers and mock definitions
    MorcParameterized
    A heavily modified version of JUnit's Parameterized class that assumes there's a public static void configure() method available to configure a set of test specifications which will then be retrieved using the getSpecifications method of MorcTest

    Any copyright for similar code will be under the EPL license for JUnit
    MorcTest
    This carries out the actual testing of the orchestrated specification specification - ensuring ordering of the received exchanges is as expected

    This will be extended for actual tests and will use JUnit Parameterized to add parameters at runtime.
